  year={2010},
  abstract={This study investigates gender differences in the willingness to compete using a large-scale experiment with 1,035 children and teenagers aged 3 to 18. The study finds that boys are significantly more likely to enter a tournament than girls across all age groups, even as young as three years old. This gender gap persists despite controlling for gender differences in risk attitudes and overconfidence, suggesting that gender differences in competitiveness emerge very early in life.},
